OL,3,CTeenager, 18, pleads guilty to
OL,4,Cmurdering his mother
OL,6,FFollowing the teenager's plea, a North
OL,7,FWales Police spokesperson said the
OL,8,Fdefendant had been "quickly identified
OL,9,Fas a suspect and he was subsequently
OL,10,Farrested at his home address" before
OL,11,Fbeing charged with murder.
OL,13,FTributes to Ms Shellis, who worked as
OL,14,Fa teaching assistant at Rhyl High
OL,15,FSchool, were paid following her tragic
OL,16,Fdeath.
OL,18,FRhyl High's headteacher Philip Collins
OL,19,Fdescribed her as "caring and
OL,20,Fcommitted".
